str2: In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.
A day, the period from sunrise to sunset.
From a compound of pro and phemi; a foreteller; by analogy, an inspired speaker; by extension, a poet.

str2: From kata and erchomai; to come down.
From, away from. A primary particle; 'off, ' i.e. Away, in various senses.
The Greek form of the Hebrew name: Jerusalem. Of Hebrew origin; Hierosolyma
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
From Antiochus; Antiochia, a place in Syria.
